### 6. **`ChatAgentToolDeps` vs `ChatToolDeps` — Type Difference**

#### **`ChatToolDeps`** (`chat/tools/types.ts`, lines 12–19)
```typescript
export type ChatToolDeps = {
  surreal: Surreal;
  embeddingModel: any;
  embeddingDimension: number;
  extractionModelId: string;
  extractionModel: any;
  extractionStoreThreshold: number;
};
```
**Used by**: Shared chat tools (search, get_project_status, create_observation) and PM tools

#### **`ChatAgentToolDeps`** (`chat/tools/types.ts`, lines 21–23)
```typescript
export type ChatAgentToolDeps = ChatToolDeps & {
  pmModel: any;
};
```
**Used by**: Chat agent tools (includes PM subagent invocation)

#### **Why This Distinction?**

| Context | Deps Type | Why |
|---------|-----------|-----|
| **Chat agent** (main orchestrator) | `ChatAgentToolDeps` | Needs `pmModel` to invoke subagent |
| **PM agent** (subagent) | `ChatToolDeps` | Gets `pmModel` from caller via `input.deps.pmModel` |
| **Shared tools** (search, status, etc.) | `ChatToolDeps` | Don't need to invoke subagents |
| **Work item accept endpoint** | Uses `ServerDependencies` | Different context (HTTP handler) |

**Key insight**: 
- `ChatToolDeps` is the **minimal set** all tools need (surreal, embeddings, extraction model)
- `ChatAgentToolDeps` adds `pmModel` for the **chat agent specifically** (because only chat agent invokes PM)
- **PM agent doesn't need `ChatAgentToolDeps`**—it receives `ChatToolDeps & { pmModel }` from caller
- This prevents circular dependency: PM agent (subagent) doesn't import chat agent types

**Why PM tool signature is `ChatToolDeps` not `ChatAgentToolDeps`**:
```typescript
// In agents/pm/agent.ts, line 52:
export type PmAgentInput = {
  deps: ChatToolDeps & { pmModel: any };  // <-- inline the pmModel, don't use ChatAgentToolDeps
  context: ChatToolExecutionContext;
  // ...
};

// In agents/pm/tools.ts, line 8:
export function createPmTools(deps: ChatToolDeps) {  // <-- just ChatToolDeps
  // PM tools use search, status, create_observation (all in ChatToolDeps)
  // PM also has create_work_item which needs extractionModel (in ChatToolDeps)
}

// But PM agent signature accepts pmModel via inline union:
export async function runPmAgent(input: PmAgentInput): Promise<PmAgentOutput> {
  const result = await generateText({
    model: input.deps.pmModel,  // <-- pmModel is in input.deps, not direct import
    // ...
  });
}
```

**Architecture benefit**: Keeps PM agent **decoupled from chat agent types**. PM agent only knows about `ChatToolDeps` + the inline pmModel, not `ChatAgentToolDeps`.

